                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="1r" to="1r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Antiphons and collects</title>
                                <rubric>Antiphona</rubric>
                                <incipit>Lauda <sic>suenigena </sic> plebs</incipit>
                                <explicit>deuota conuersacione et placitis moribus deseruire Qui viuis et regnas in deo patre in vnitate spiritus sancti deus per omnia secula seculorum Amen </explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="1r" to="1r" scheme="folios"/> records a miscellany of antiphons and prayers related to Birgitta and Katarina. The first four antihphons recorded on <locus from="1r" to="1r" scheme="folios"/> are found again, with musical notation and in a different medieval hand, on <locus from="63r" to="63r" scheme="folios"/> and <locus from="64r" to="64v" scheme="folios"/>.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="1v" to="1v" scheme="folios"/> blank.</p>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="2r" to="63r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Processional for the Birgittine liturgy</title>
                                <incipit>Regnum mundi et omnen ornatum</incipit>
                                <explicit>Gloria patri et filio et spiritui santo</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p>
                                        The contents of the processional - antiphons, responsories, tropes, glorie, and hymns – is printed by Geete as <quote>Cantus sororum</quote> in his edition of the Birgittine liturgy as preserved in Stockholm, National Library, A 12; A 92a follows a different order from Geete's edition.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="14" to="14" scheme="folios"/> has been incorrectly placed, resulting in a disruption in the order of the text; the correct placement of <locus from="14" to="14" scheme="folios"/> is after <locus from="15" to="15" scheme="folios"/>. The misplacement is signalled by signes-de-renvoi on <locus from="13v" to="13v" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="14r" to="14v" scheme="folios"/>, and <locus from="15r" to="15v" scheme="folios"/>, with explanatory notes in German.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        The last couple of items – two responsories, each with a following verse (<locus from="61r" to="62v" scheme="folios"/>), for Maccabees, highlighted by the marginal note <quote>Contra Turcas</quote>, and a gloria in a different medieval hand (<locus from="62v" to="62v" scheme="folios"/>) – are not included in Geete. <!--(EJ 100%!!!)--></p>
                                </note>
                                <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107252">Geete (1895)</title>
                                    <citedRange from="209" to="267" unit="page"/>
                                </bibl>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="63r" to="63r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Antiphon</title>
                                <rubric>V<supplied reason="omitted">ersi</supplied>o sant katherina</rubric>
                                <incipit>O patrone ingenue</incipit>
                                <explicit>perspicue a clade repentina</explicit>
                                <filiation>
                                    <idno type="msRef"/>
                                </filiation>
                                <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107275">Collijn (1945)</title>
                                    <citedRange from="66" to="66" unit="page"/>
                                </bibl>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="63v" to="64r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc" xml:lang="de">Gospel readings in German</title>
                                <incipit>An dem grünen donderstag</incipit>
                                <explicit xml:lang="de">dat auch ir also einander thut</explicit>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="64r" to="64r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Antiphon</title>
                                <incipit>Birgitta vas gracie</incipit>
                                <explicit>per suffragia Saluemur a ruina</explicit>
                                <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107297">Collijn (1945)</title>
                                    <citedRange from="66" to="66" unit="page"/>
                                </bibl>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="64v" to="64v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Antiphon</title>
                                <incipit>Lauda suecigena plebs</incipit>
                                <explicit>semper exaltat katherine</explicit>
                                <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107297">Collijn (1945)</title>
                                    <citedRange from="65" to="65" unit="page"/>
                                </bibl>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="64v" to="64v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Antiphon</title>
                                <incipit>Uale mater inclita</incipit>
                                <explicit>et celorum abdita</explicit>
                                <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107297">Collijn (1945)</title>
                                    <citedRange from="65" to="65" unit="page"/>
                                </bibl>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="65r" to="68r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <textLang mainLang="de" otherLangs="la"/>
                                <title type="desc">Index</title>
                                <rubric xml:lang="de">Hye nach folgt dat register vber diez processional an welchen tagen dat obgeschriben gesanck gehalten wirt mit sampt einer zal an welchem plat ein yeglich responsz oder antiffen geschriben vnd notiert ist </rubric>
                                <note>
                                    <p>
                                        The index is organised by rubrics, in German, for each feast day; under each rubric follows the incipits of the material to be sung, in order, followed by the contemporary folio number on which the item in question is found.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="68v" to="68v" scheme="folios"/> Guidelines but no text.</p>
                                </note>
                                <colophon>
                                    <locus from="68r" to="68r" scheme="folios"/>Laus deo finis in die felicitate anno 1499 Bit got auch fur mich</colophon>
                            </msItem>
